        <mxCell id="CG8b47xFTE-a7-1MDE-e-304" parent="CG8b47xFTE-a7-1MDE-e-303" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;hachureGap=4;fontFamily=Mali;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#F9EBFF;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;labelBorderColor=none;textShadow=0;labelBackgroundColor=none;align=left;spacing=5;verticalAlign=middle;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DMali;arcSize=11;" value="&lt;div&gt;This replaces transformed features with a simple kernel evaluation in the original space.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="259.76464277332616" x="0.23535722667380318" y="170" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="CG8b47xFTE-a7-1MDE-e-305" parent="CG8b47xFTE-a7-1MDE-e-303" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;hachureGap=4;fontFamily=Mali;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#F9EBFF;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;labelBorderColor=none;textShadow=0;labelBackgroundColor=none;align=left;spacing=5;verticalAlign=middle;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DMali;arcSize=8;spacingTop=10;" value="&lt;div&gt;The dual SVM algorithm only needs to compute inner products of the form:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;math-block&quot; data-math=&quot;\langle\phi(\mathbf{x}_i), \phi(\mathbf{x}_j)\rangle&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Google Sans Text, sans-serif !important; line-height: 1.15 !important; margin-top: 0px !important;&quot;&gt;$$\langle\phi(\mathbf{x}_i), \phi(\mathbf{x}_j)\rangle$$&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="70" width="259.76464277332616" y="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="CG8b47xFTE-a7-1MDE-e-306" parent="CG8b47xFTE-a7-1MDE-e-303" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;hachureGap=4;fontFamily=Mali;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=13;fontStyle=0;labelBorderColor=none;textShadow=0;labelBackgroundColor=none;align=left;spacing=5;verticalAlign=middle;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DMali;arcSize=11;" value="The Kernel Trick – The Smart Shortcut" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="259.76464277332616" x="0.23535722667380318" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="CG8b47xFTE-a7-1MDE-e-307" parent="CG8b47xFTE-a7-1MDE-e-303" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;hachureGap=4;fontFamily=Mali;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#F9EBFF;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;labelBorderColor=none;textShadow=0;labelBackgroundColor=none;align=left;spacing=5;verticalAlign=middle;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DMali;arcSize=8;spacingTop=10;" value="&lt;div&gt;A kernel function directly evaluates this inner product without calculating `\phi(\mathbf{x})`:$$K(\mathbf{x}_i, \mathbf{x}_j) = \langle\phi(\mathbf{x}_i), \phi(\mathbf{x}_j)\rangle$$&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="70" width="259.76464277332616" y="100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
